=== Precincts ===
[[File:Obori-jinja honden.JPG|thumb|250px|right|Main sanctuary (Takasaki City-designated Important Cultural Property)]]
The current main shrine buildings consist of main sanctuary, heiden, and worship hall in an integrated form. However, the heiden and worship hall were built later than the main sanctuary. Documents and dedication plaques indicate reconstruction was planned in Shōtoku 3 ({{ill|lt=1713|Q6873|WD=Q6873|1=1713}}) and ridge-raising completed in Kyōhō 2 ({{ill|lt=1717|Q6895|WD=Q6895|1=1717}}). The style is three-bay {{ill|lt=irimoya-zukuri|Q855025|WD=Q855025|1=East Asian hip-and-gable roof}}, with three bays on the sides and a three-bay front kōhai. The roof is now copper plate, though originally likely {{ill|lt=hiwada-buki|Q90373477|WD=Q90373477|1=cypress bark roof}} or kokera-buki. Interior is divided into outer chamber (front two bays) and inner sanctuary (rear one bay), with a {{ill|lt=zushi|Q19993032|WD=Q19993032|1=Zushi}} installed in the inner sanctuary. This main sanctuary is the oldest shrine main sanctuary in Takasaki, and its rear inset carved panel (oldest example in Gunma) serves as a chronological benchmark for similar works; with munafuda, dedication plaque, and donor inscription it is designated Takasaki City Important Cultural Property<ref>Precinct explanation board.</ref><ref name="本殿"/>{{Sfn|小祝神社（式内社）|1986年}}.

